HEADWORD: Succursal
<hw>Suc*cur"sal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>succursale</ets>. See <er>Succor</er>, <pos>n.</pos> & <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <def>Serving to aid or help; serving as a chapel of
ease; tributary.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not a city was without its cathedral, surrounded by its
<qex>succursal</qex> churches, its monasteries, and convents.</q>
<rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Succus</ent>⟦br⟧
